For 21 years Georges Bwelle saw how his sick father lost the consciousness again and again and traveled to hospitals which did not have the means in order to help him.
Jamef Bwelle was hurt by Yaoundé, the capital of Cameroon, in 1981 at a car accident near.
First he had only a broken arm, however, then an inflammation which expanded onto his brain and a Hämatom which should influence it for the rest of his life caused there formed itself.
„There were not any neurosurgeons in Cameroon", according to Georges Bwelle.
We would have brought it out from Cameroon if we had had the money.
Instead of this Bwelle spent years with accompanying his father in full clinics and hospitals in order to get the treatment which they had to offer there.
